{"type":"message","id":"c656be8f","parentId":"211068b8","timestamp":"2026-04-06T00:59:30.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'm getting a clearer picture. Let me look at the experiment registry to see what strategies exist and which ones have higher returns than the 55.07% baseline. The `rd_agent_top2_gray_v1` shows 48.18% annual return which is lower than 55.07%.\n\nActually, I see from the experiment registry:\n- `rd_agent_top2_gray_v1`: 48.18% annual return (retired_candidate, lower than 55.07%)\n\nBut wait - the user is asking about a \"higher return strategy\" that already exists. Let me check if there's something I'm missing. \n\nThe governance gate only shows smallcap_chip strategies and rd_agent strategies. The 55.07% strategy (\"Qlib breadth + turnover hardcap relaxed\") appears to be coming from the audit system. Looking at the experiment registry, none of the listed strategies actually exceed 55.07% annual return - the best performer is rd_agent_top2_gray_v1 at 48.18%, while the smallcap_chip variants are all below 25%. I need to figure out where the 55.07% baseline is actually coming from and whether there's a higher-return strategy already implemented that I'm not seeing in this registry.\n\nLet me check the paper profiles comparison metrics and the latest overnight report to see if there's a different strategy tier or if the 55.07% figure represents something different than what I'm looking at.","thinkingSignature":"22b7e66c8a1d50a029bccb232051125c6e36a8dccbad9c8fc72de44e2a8d261e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6w5elczslt4t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/paper_profiles_comparison_metrics_20260323.json 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects -name \"paper_profiles_comparison*\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_functi