{"type":"message","id":"28d8e005","parentId":"282cb7e7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T01:00:01.724Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the situation better. The 55.07% is the annualized return of the \"Qlib breadth + turnover hardcap relaxed\" strategy - this is the **current active strategy** that the system uses as its main strategy.\n\nThe user is asking: \"Why are we still using the 55% strategy as baseline when there's already a higher return strategy?\"\n\nLooking at the experiment registry:\n- `smallcap_chip_v4_1_alpha_guard`: candidate, 20.99% OOS\n- `smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover`: watch_candidate, 22.0% OOS\n- `rd_agent_top2_gray_v1`: retired_candidate, 48.18% annual return\n\n\n- The walk-forward aggressive variant shows 25.60% annual return with Sharpe 1.625\n\nNone of these actually exceed the 55% baseline - they're all significantly lower. So either the user is referring to something I haven't found yet, or they're mistaken about what the higher-return strategy actually is. The 55% strategy is labeled as the baseline in the audit reports, but I need to check if there's another strategy with better performance that I'm missing in the governance gate files.\n\nLooking at the current governance state, the 55% strategy appears to be the stable approved strategy generating these returns. The other candidates are all underperforming - the walk-forward aggressive is at 25.60%, the rd_agent_top2_gray_v1 is at 48.18%, and the smallcap_chip variants are all below 23%. There's a fundamental_guard variant too that hasn't been tested yet. I'm not seeing anything that would actually be higher than the 55% baseline.\n\nThe user's statement that a higher-return strategy already exists doesn't match what I'm seeing in the experiment registry. Either they're referring to something not in the registry, or there's been a conversation about a strategy that was never actually committed. The 55.07% strategy appears to be the only one actually delivering those kinds of returns.\n\nI should ask the user to clarify which strategy they're referring to, since the governance data shows the candidate strategies all have significantly lower returns. I need to look at what the user is actually referring to—there might be a strategy in the system that isn't showing up in the governance reports, or perhaps something was discussed in an earlier conversation that I haven't found yet. Let me reconsider the experiment registry data more carefully to see if there's a candidate or archived strategy that could match what they're describing.","thinkingSignature":"8a20f0882c5092f7ede787a9e4e77956cab4c59812e12523c2b0e21154269cb7"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 好问题，我顺着你的问题去翻了系统里所有策略的收益数据，结果如下：\n\n**你说的\"更高收益策略\"——我目前在系统里没有找到比 55.07% 更高的实盘候选。**\n\n| 策略 | 状态 | 年化收益 | Sharpe | 回撤 |\n|------|------|---------|--------|------|\n| Qlib breadth+turnover（当前基准） | ✅ 稳定运行 | **55.07%** | 2.794 | 24.89% |\n| rd_agent_top2_gray_v1 | 已下线候选 | 48.18% | 1.976 | 19.46% |\n| smallcap_walk_forward_aggressive | 回测 | 25.60% | 1.625 | 8.13% |\n| smallcap_chip_v4_2_alpha_recover | 观察候选 | 22.0%（OOS均值） | 1.687 | 6.37% |\n| smallcap_chip_v4_1_alpha_guard | 候选 | 20.99%（OOS均值） | 1.617 | 6.48% |\n\n---\n\n**结论：55.07% 是目前所有候选里最高的。**\n\n你说的\"更高收益策略\"——能告诉我是哪个吗？可能是：\n\n1. **不在 experiment_registry 里的策略**（直接回测文件跑的，没进治理链）\n2. **更早期的版本**（后来被更高参数覆盖了）\n3. **还是你在问的是一个应该存在但还没做出来的策略**？\n\n给我一个名字或者来源，我马上核实。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27420,"output":846,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49733,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775437182560,"responseId":"0622387e7b848cf3700106b6dd750fd2"}}
