{"type":"message","id":"bab30808","parentId":"80879fff","timestamp":"2026-04-06T05:37:37.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `run_daily_investment_research_brief.py` and `run_premarket_risk_v2.py` don't have `is_trading_day()` checks. They rely on `1-5` in the cron schedule, which includes public holidays.\n\nThe issue is clear: the cron schedule uses `1-5` (Monday to Friday) which doesn't account for Chinese public holidays like Qingming Festival (April 4-6).\n\nI should fix this by adding a `is_trading_day()` check to the pre-market briefing script so it skips on non-trading days.\n\nLet me look at how `is_trading_day()` is implemented in the other scripts:","thinkingSignature":"f9ede62f35aae973cddeddb8ed9f3acc284f60e70b65e7b7fb21babdea82a1b5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2zg1j2aamtc8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 20 \"def is_trading_day\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/generate_actionable_brief.py 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34966,"output":196,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56629,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775453852038,"responseId":"0622799c42d372db81116cbbd1dd4fb8"}}
