{"type":"message","id":"f13f1ed7","parentId":"0decd945","timestamp":"2026-04-06T05:39:04.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `cron_daily_investment_research_brief.sh` is indeed the wrapper that runs `run_daily_investment_research_brief.py`. And from the log I can see the `investment_research_brief_morning.log` shows it ran today at 08:30. But the cron for the morning brief was set to `30 08 * * 1-5` (08:30), while the pre-open briefing that the user was replying to was dated 08:40.\n\nWait, the user's message is replying to a \"📋 来福投研会盘前值班汇报（2026-04-06 08:40）\" - this 08:40 briefing might be from a different cron. \n\nLooking at the cron list, I can see `investment-research-background-preopen-0840 08:40来福投研会-盘前值班` with a different schedule `40 8 * * 1-5 @ Asia/Shanghai`. But the user got the 08:40 report, and my fix should prevent the `run_daily_investment_research_brief.py` from running today. I need to check what triggered at 08:40.","thinkingSignature":"75151de0e7d0187900b706df84be3b404b2b74f30c5550be95b511e7c82f6739"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rrhyzbhzikrs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"premarket\\|pre_open\\|preopen\\|盘前.*值班\\|值班.*盘前\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".pyc\" | grep -v \"cron_python\\|run_daily\\|render_daily\\|build_daily\\|manage_daily\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rrhyzbhzikrs_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts -maxdepth 1 -name \"*.py\" -o -name \"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | sort"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42494,"output":426,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64387,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775453935735,"resp