{"type":"message","id":"7b78a6a7","parentId":"74d3071c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T05:41:38.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`requests` is available. Let me use a simple approach - check against a well-known calendar. Actually, let me try the simplest approach: use a Tencent or Baidu API to check if the market is open today.Actually, I think the most pragmatic approach is:1. Check if today is a weekend (already done)\n2. Check if today is in a list of major Chinese A-share holidays for 2026Let me just add a simple hardcoded check for known 2026 holidays. It's not perfect but it's better than nothing.China's 2026 official holidays:\n- 元旦: Jan 1, 2026 (Thursday) - holiday Jan 1\n\n\n- 春节: Feb 15-21, 2026 (Spring Festival holiday), with Feb 22 (Sunday) as a makeup workday\n- 清明节: April 4-6, 2026 (Saturday-Monday)\n- 劳动节: May 1-3, 2026 (Friday-Sunday)\n- 端午节: May 31 - June 2, 2026 (Sunday-Tuesday)\n- 中秋节: October 1-3, 2026 (Thursday-Saturday)\n- 国庆节: October 1-7, 2026 (Thursday-Wednesday), with September 28 (Monday) and October 10 (Saturday) as makeup workdays\n\nI should implement a proper holiday checking function instead of hardcoding dates, but I'll start with this approach and refine it later. I'm going to check whether the A-share market is actually open today by testing a financial data API, since I can't reliably determine trading days from the available calendar data.","thinkingSignature":"edfa79e51329943ad87eddfe9932b186b9a7d921fa8c4975595989cf2cef05c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t4y7dg8dd8hr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport requests, datetime\ntoday = datetime.date(2026, 4, 6)\n# Try Tencent market API - if market is closed, today's data won't be available\ntry:\n    r = requests.get(f'https://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001', timeout=5)\n    lines = r.text.strip().split(';')\n    for line in lines:\n        if 'sh000001' in line:\n            parts = line.split('~')\n            if len(parts) > 3:\n                date_str = parts[30] if len(parts) > 30 else ''\n                price = parts[3] if len(parts) > 3 else ''\n                print(f'上证指数日期字段: {date_str}, 价格: {price}')\n                break\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f'Error: {e}')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":59707,"output":556,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775454083487,"responseId":"06227a831ee77c587f0a93da6a3d8cff"}}
