{"type":"message","id":"2c54d6c4","parentId":"51f5b910","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:18:04.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking: regardless of the 68% strategy, can we use the 58% strategy (58.48% walk-forward OOS) as the reference strategy for the quantitative analyst role? \n\nLooking at the governance system, the current benchmark for the quant_analyst role is the 55.07% strategy (\"Qlib breadth + turnover hardcap relaxed\"). The 58.48% walk-forward strategy has better metrics.\n\nThe question is about whether the quant analyst role briefing can use the 58.48% strategy as its reference/baseline instead of the 55.07% one. This is a legitimate question about updating the baseline reference for the role.\n\n\nNow I need to locate where the quant_analyst role pulls its reference metrics from—likely the duty roster config—and check the governance files to understand how the benchmark is set.","thinkingSignature":"b0e881376d6214147f6f6d6033696c3b7a361e9354788b0e5bf0dcc7171cd6f8"},{"type":"text","text":"可以，但需要先确认这个 58.48% 策略的 registry 状态和治理定位，然后更新配置。让我先查一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4cas28oo70ub_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/experiment_registry_v1.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor exp in d.get('experiments', []):\n    metrics = exp.get('latest_oos_metrics', {})\n    ann = metrics.get('test_annual_return_pct_mean', 0)\n    if ann > 55:\n        print(f\\\"ID: {exp['strategy_id']}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  state: {exp.get('strategy_state', '?')}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  ann_return: {ann:.2f}%\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  sharpe: {metrics.get('test_sharpe_mean', '?')}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  max_dd: {metrics.get('test_max_drawdown_pct_mean', '?')}\\\")\n        print(f\\\"  folds: {metrics.get('test_folds', '?')}\\\")\n        print()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-