{"type":"message","id":"4cd1583a","parentId":"ebc0bcff","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:18:51.276Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's a note in `stock_alpha_v3_qlib_breadth_hardcap_relaxed.yaml` that says \"switched from risk_degree=0.50(55.07%) on 2026-04-04; higher breadth sensitivity + stop-loss added (breadth_emergency=0.20, dd_soft=0.10, dd_hard=0.20)\". This suggests that the strategy was already switched on 2026-04-04. Let me check this file to see what's currently running.\n\nActually, the user's earlier message said: \"新稳定策略参数（已确认）：topk=8, risk_degree=0.80, daily_turnover_cap=0.28, ... Walk-Forward OOS: 年化 58.48%, 回撤 9.05%, 正收益窗口 9/9\"\n\n\nSo they've already switched to the 58.48% strategy with those exact parameters. The question now is whether the 55.07% baseline in the governance files needs updating to reflect this new strategy, or if it should remain as a benchmark comparison.\n\nLooking at the strategy governance notes, the current approved strategy is `smallcap_chip_v4` with 55.07% returns. But the user has a new candidate with 58.48% that performed better on walk-forward analysis with lower drawdown. The governance system seems to be tracking the old strategy while the user has already moved to the new one.\n\nThe user is asking whether the quantitative analyst can reference the new 58.48% strategy instead of the 55.07% baseline. I should check if this new strategy has been properly registered in the experiment registry and whether it can serve as a valid reference point for the analyst's work. I need to dig into the governance configuration to understand what criteria determine whether a strategy qualifies as a valid candidate.","thinkingSignature":"a1d456260f72adb4df0ad36dce10120775ed52ed562f8bf3856fde068fb7c834"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7xnphlrtdzfi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/strategy_registry_v2.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor s in d.get('strategies', []):\n    sid = s.get('strategy_id','')\n    ann = s.get('latest_oos_metrics', {}).get('test_annual_return_pct_mean', 0)\n    state = s.get('strategy_state','')\n    if ann > 0 or 'aggressive' in sid or '58' in str(ann):\n        print(f'{sid}: state={state}, OOS_ann={ann:.2f}%')\nprint()\nprint('All strategies:')\nfor s in d.get('strategies', []):\n    print(f'  {s[\\\"strategy_id\\\"]}: {s.get(\\\"strategy_state\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69895,"output":602,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91964,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775456316874,"responseId":"0622833daeb9557daadb441f7473233b"}}
