{"type":"message","id":"ab46e5f4","parentId":"bbfbf941","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:31:22.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create the `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json` - the live trading execution config with v4.3 params. I'll base it on the existing `paper_live_trading_aggressive_v1.json` structure but with the v4.3 strategy params from the Qlib config.\n\nLooking at the existing `paper_live_trading_aggressive_v1.json`, the main things that differ for v4.3 are:\n1. The `smallcap_live_candidates` section - but actually v4.3 is a Qlib breadth strategy, not a YAML smallcap_chip strategy\n2. I need to figure out how to make the paper trading use Qlib breadth strategy signals\n\n\n3. Since the paper trading pulls from `signals/merged/merged_signals_{date}.csv` which gets populated by the Qlib signal generation pipeline, I should create a `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json` that mirrors the live trading v1 config with v4.3 params, set `smallcap_live_candidates` to null or point to a config that uses Qlib breadth strategy, and ensure the Qlib pipeline writes signals to the right location.\n\nActually, the cleaner approach is to just update the existing `smallcap_live_candidates` to use the Qlib breadth strategy since the signal generation already routes based on config. I could either point it to the v4.3 Qlib params directly, or create a wrapper that references the live trading v4.3 config, though that might break the YAML-based smallcap_chip pipeline that's currently in use.\n\nLooking at how `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` actually reads signals from `merged_signals_{date}.csv` and generates orders, I realize the `smallcap_live_candidates.config` field is more of a labeling mechanism for candidate reports rather than the actual signal source. So I should create `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json` as a proper live trading config with Qlib v4.3 params, set `smallcap_live_candidates.config` to the Qlib config path, and ensure the signal generation pipeline writes to the correct merged signals file that paper trading reads from. Actually, the `smallcap_live_candidates` section in the live trading config is primarily used by the live trading system (run_live_system_v1.py), not the paper trading system. The paper trading system (`run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py`) reads from the merged signals file.\n\nSo the key question is: does the merged signals file contain v4.3 strategy signals? Looking at how the signals are generated - the `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` reads from merged signals, which come from the signal generation pipeline. The Qlib signal generation pipeline would need to generate v4.3 signals.\n\nThe simplest approach for paper trading with v4.3 is to create the config files pointing to v4.3 params, then run the Qlib signal generation to populate the merged signals file for the next trading day, and the paper trading system will automatically pick up those signals on the following day. I'll model `paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json` after the existing live trading config.","thinkingSignature":"37b669bfee759b7a60c7727f10dfc8c0f4c24c9dc563703f60df6d672c737f9c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0epe0hh7okd4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/config/paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json << 'EOF'\n{\n  \"market\": \"CN_A\",\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"exclude_st\": true,\n    \"min_listing_days\": 120,\n    \"benchmark_smallcap\": \"ZZ2000\",\n    \"benchmark_broad\": \"HS300\"\n  },\n  \"targets\": {\n    \"annual_return_min_pct\": 40.0,\n    \"max_drawdown_max_pct\": 25.0\n  },\n  \"execution\": {\n    \"lot_size\": 100,\n    \"max_daily_add_ratio\": 0.5,\n    \"single_ticket_budget_ratio_of_available_cash\": 0.15,\n    \"max_single_position_ratio\": 0.18,\n    \"cash_buffer_ratio\": 0.08,\n    \"buy_window\": \"09:45-10:30\",\n    \"risk_only_after\": \"10:30\"\n  },\n  \"execution_decision\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"buy_signal_score_weight\": 0.8,\n    \"buy_intraday_score_weight\": 0.2,\n    \"buy_intraday_floor_pct\": -2.0,\n    \"buy_intraday_ceiling_pct\": 2.0,\n    \"buy_realtime_drop_soft_penalty_pct\": -3.0,\n    \"buy_realtime_drop_hard_block_pct\": -5.0,\n    \"buy_realtime_drop_score_scale\": 0.35,\n    \"buy_realtime_drop_position_scale\": 0.25,\n    \"buy_intraday_ma_exception_enabled\": true,\n    \"buy_intraday_ma_exception_window\": 20,\n    \"buy_intraday_ma_exception_min_bias_pct\": 0.0,\n    \"buy_intraday_ma_exception_score_scale\": 0.6,\n    \"buy_intraday_ma_exception_position_scale\": 0.5,\n    \"buy_signal_score_floor\": 0.56\n  },\n  \"risk\": {\n    \"single_soft_stop_pct\": -8.0,\n    \"single_hard_stop_pct\": -10.0,\n    \"portfolio_drawdown_guard_pct\": -5.0,\n    \"portfolio_drawdown_halt_pct\": -6.0,\n    \"index_halt_threshold_pct\": -2.0,\n    \"weekly_loss_trigger_pct\": -7.0,\n    \"riskoff_total_exposure\": 0.8,\n    \"allow_new_buy_when_riskoff\": true,\n    \"market_breadth_riskoff_threshold\": 0.25,\n    \"market_breadth_hard_stop_threshold\": 0.20,\n    \"strategy_sharpe_cautious_threshold\": 0.6,\n    \"mode_halt_target_exposure\": 0.35,\n    \"cautious_probe\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"max_daily_add_ratio_of_available_cash\": 0.2,\n      \"single_ticket_budget_ratio_of_available_cash\": 0.08,\n      \"max_single_position_ratio\": 0.08,\n      \"max_buy_slots\": 5\n    },\n    \"style_rotation\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"short_window\": 5,\n      \"medium_window\": 20,\n      \"riskoff_short_excess_pct\": -2.0,\n      \"riskoff_medium_excess_pct\": -4.0,\n      \"hard_stop_short_excess_pct\": -4.0,\n      \"hard_stop_medium_excess_pct\": -6.0,\n      \"hard_stop_requires_negative_smallcap\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"cost\": {\n    \"commission_rate\": 8.5e-05,\n    \"min_commission\": 0,\n    \"stamp_duty_sell\": 0.001,\n    \"slippage_bps\": 8\n  },\n  \"qlib_breadth_long_b_v1\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"as_of_date\": \"20260404\",\n    \"period\": {\n      \"start_date\": \"2015-01-05\",\n      \"end_date\": \"2026-03-03\"\n    },\n    \"sanity_rules\": {\n      \"signal_shift\": \"T+1\",\n      \"deal_price\": \"open\",\n      \"open_cost\": 0.000885,\n      \"close_cost\": 0.001885,\n      \"breadth_use\": \"previous_day\"\n    },\n    \"params\": {\n      \"topk\": 8,\n      \"n_drop\": 1,\n      \"hold_thresh\": 4,\n      \"risk_degree\": 0.80,\n      \"min_score_improve\": 0.0,\n      \"daily_turnover_cap\": 0.28,\n      \"breadth_low_th\": 0.45,\n      \"breadth_mid_th\": 0.55,\n      \"breadth_low_scale\": 0.40,\n      \"breadth_mid_scale\": 0.70,\n      \"breadth_high_scale\": 1.0,\n      \"breadth_emergency_th\": 0.20,\n      \"dd_soft\": 0.10,\n      \"dd_hard\": 0.20\n    }\n  },\n  \"exit_rules\": {\n    \"trailing_take_profit_arm_pct\": 12.0,\n    \"trailing_take_profit_drawdown_pct\": 6.0,\n    \"trailing_take_profit_confirm_bars\": 1\n  },\n  \"smallcap_live_candidates\": {\n    \"profile\": \"v4_3_aggressive\",\n    \"config\": \"config/live_trading_v1.json\",\n    \"main_count\": 10,\n    \"guard_count\": 8,\n    \"main_target_weight\": 0.1,\n    \"guard_target_weight\": 0.08,\n    \"note\": \"小市值筹码v4.3进取型：Walk-Forward OOS年化58.48%，使用Qlib breadth+turnover策略参数\"\n  },\n  \"feature_flags\": {\n    \"dual_factor_profile\": \"off\"\n  },\n  \"_strategy_note\": \"paper版对应 live_trading_v1.json 的 qlib_breadth_long_b_v1 params，v4.3进取型参数：topk=8/risk_degree=0.80/turnover_cap=0.28/breadth新阈值/止损强化\"\n}\nEOF\necho \"paper_live_trading_v4_3_v1.json 创建完成\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94796,"output":2120,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":118383,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775457048289,"responseId":"06228618af086247c903cfaa30d6bb7e"}}
