{"type":"message","id":"f4689a1f","parentId":"bf6b7984","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:31:04.792Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is \"open_id cross app\" - the open_id is from a different app. The app_id `cli_a928c429d9785cc6` is associated with a different user/open_id than `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae`.\n\nLooking at the openclaw.json, there are multiple accounts:\n- `main`: appId=cli_a928c429d9785cc6\n- `feishu-assistant`: appId=cli_a9256a7ae9b91cb6\n- `coding-agent`: appId=cli_a934da0dde385cba\n  \nI need to find which app is actually associated with the user's open_id and switch to that one instead of trying to use the main account.","thinkingSignature":"87534aee2143add86afeff0cd9d5c286391f133659630372ef13004d8cb0281d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wr151vsa7s4x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nopenclaw_cfg = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'openclaw.json'\ndata = json.loads(openclaw_cfg.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\nfeishu_cfg = data.get('channels', {}).get('feishu', {})\naccounts = feishu_cfg.get('accounts', {})\ndefault = feishu_cfg.get('defaultAccount', '')\nprint('default account:', default)\nfor k,v in accounts.items():\n    print(f'  {k}: appId={v.get(\\\"appId\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\nprint()\nprint('Full feishu config:')\nprint(json.dumps(feishu_cfg, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106664,"output":352,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128483,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775475052947,"responseId":"0622cc6d5b51ab45ec5986298016a5b9"}}
