{"type":"message","id":"799dcfd2","parentId":"bff75175","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:38:20.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"I've already configured it, otherwise how were the previous scheduled tasks able to push?\" - they're referring to the Feishu push mechanism. The issue is that the openclaw CLI `message send` command fails with \"open_id cross app\" error. But the cron jobs do successfully push to Feishu.\n\nThis means the cron jobs must be using a different mechanism - probably the `message` tool or a different API approach. Let me look at how existing scripts push to Feishu.\n\nActually, I think I know what's happening. The cron scripts push via the OpenClaw cron system's announcement mechanism (when they run as sub-agents), not via direct Feishu API calls. The sub-agent runs within OpenClaw's context where it has access to the Feishu channel through the message tool.\n \nSo the solution is to either have the audit script run as a sub-agent within the cron system so it can use the message tool directly, or set up a flag file approach where the script writes its output and I'm notified to send it manually. But the user is saying the push mechanism is already configured and working, so there must be something else I'm missing about how the existing cron jobs actually deliver their messages.\n\nLooking at the flag file pattern - I've confirmed that the `message` tool works when I call it directly, but the OpenClaw CLI can't send to that specific open_id because it belongs to a different app. The real cron jobs probably bypass this by either running as sub-agents with access to the message tool, or by using the OpenClaw cron announcement system which handles the Feishu delivery internally. I should just ask the user directly how the existing scripts are configured to push.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - the cleanest solution would be to make the audit script a sub-agent cron job rather than a shell script. That way the sub-agent inherits my Feishu identity and can use the message tool directly. But the user asked me to configure it, and I should respect that constraint. Let me focus on explaining the open_id cross-app issue more clearly and suggest the sub-agent approach as the most straightforward way forward.","thinkingSignature":"fa98710f3381ad376c781ad93aff4dc296490c0360a17208e27208a5cc4d7159"},{"type":"text","text":"你说得对，我来仔细看一下现有的推送是怎么实现的：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9n6e5w2sgev5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -60 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py | grep -A 30 \"push\\|feishu\\|message\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9n6e5w2sgev5_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"openclaw cron add\\|--announce\\|--deliver\\|--message\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/cron_daily_investment_research_brief.sh 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74,"output":589,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":110809,"totalTokens":132939,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775475481547,"responseId":"0622ce19133ffdb0504df5d153233d8a"}}
