{"type":"message","id":"d0753c59","parentId":"99c829f4","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:47:44.319Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user confirmed they received the test message and wants it pushed to the Feishu private chat. I need to update the target to `user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` (their current Feishu open_id). But we know that `openclaw message send` to `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` fails with \"open_id cross app\" error. However, the `message` tool (which I'm using right now) works fine to this open_id.\nThe key difference is that OpenClaw uses the Lark SDK directly, which can handle the cross-app scenario, while the CLI's webhook approach doesn't. So I need to check whether the `report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py` script actually succeeds when using the `openclaw message send` command with this open_id.","thinkingSignature":"fe36b04977ac781fcbe657b7310345fb29addc25c6390a8457012986f7ff9d4e"},{"type":"text","text":"好，把推送目标改成你的私聊 ID `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae`。但之前直接用 CLI 推这个 ID 会报 cross-app 错误，不过我刚发给你的消息成功了——说明我用 `message` 工具的方式可以直达。让我验证一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j6zyxxtgpkl1_1","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"feishu","target":"user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae","message":"测试：这条是直接推到你私聊的吗？收到请回复"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74,"output":360,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":108943,"totalTokens":130844,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476049541,"responseId":"0622d052a221976411cc94f53c726f05"}}
