{"type":"message","id":"424a8e77","parentId":"3d2ff9ae","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:48:01.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can send to `user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` via the `message` tool. Now the question is how to make the cron script send to this ID.\n\nThe issue is that the cron runs as a background process, not within this session. So I can't directly use the `message` tool from within the cron script.\n\nBut I can use the OpenClaw SDK's `sendMessageFeishu` function from Python. Let me look at how to import and use it.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully:\n- The cron job runs as an \"isolated\" session\n\n\n- The message tool works because it's running in the context of my current session\n- The background cron script can't use the message tool directly\n\nI could call `openclaw message send` via subprocess, but that fails with cross-app. However, I noticed I can send directly to `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` using the message tool, so there might be a way to invoke this from the cron script using the OpenClaw SDK or a specific CLI command.\n\nI found that `sendMessageFeishu` is exported from the openclaw-lark extension. Let me try using subprocess to call the message tool directly with the right target ID.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the real issue: this current session uses account A (the coding-agent) to send messages to Zhang Ling's ID, but the cron job runs under a different account (the main session's feishu account). If I use the message tool in the cron script via subprocess, it should still work since it's running in the OpenClaw context.\n\nBut `openclaw message send` via subprocess fails with \"open_id cross app\" even though the `message` tool itself works. The difference is that `message` uses the Lark SDK with the correct cross-app configuration, while the CLI command doesn't have access to that same setup.\n\nI could try installing the openclaw-lark package and calling its APIs directly from Python, or just run a cron job that wakes up the main session and lets it handle the message sending instead.","thinkingSignature":"4e6d0a47d88fb9e6505f17f48cd336fcbfb03b3881e405042363da307035a187"},{"type":"text","text":"收到了！消息工具可以直接推到你私聊。现在问题是 cron 在后台跑，不能直接用 `message` 工具。我用 OpenClaw 的 Lark SDK 来发，它和 message 工具是同一套账号体系：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pex0hb6n3io5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/node_modules/@larksuite -name \"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/node_modules/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109457,"output":592,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131516,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476064971,"responseId":"0622d061394b8d083e960efaf58a799e"}}
