{"type":"message","id":"b6481eeb","parentId":"b6cad2ef","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:48:45.983Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, the config has `channels.feishu` but it's spelled differently. Let me try to create a Lark SDK client and send a message.\n\nActually, the key insight is: the `message` tool in this session CAN send to `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae`. This is because the current session is authenticated with the correct app credentials that can send to this user.\n\nThe cron script runs in an \"isolated\" session. But it doesn't use the same credentials? Actually, it uses the same openclaw.json. But `openclaw message send` CLI command fails with cross-app, while the `message` tool succeeds.\n \nI'm thinking the issue might be that when the cron session calls `openclaw message send` via subprocess, it's using the gateway's auth context instead of the session's context, which could be running under different credentials. Let me write a Node.js script that directly uses the Lark SDK with the credentials from openclaw.json to see if that bypasses the cross-app restriction.","thinkingSignature":"adac0419a2abbc5f97f729ccaa7e44e8ddd694e6b93db93c4cc7abeee50b89b4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iq3x6p1kmgf0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > /tmp/test_lark_send.js << 'EOF'\nconst { Client, Domain } = require('/Users/ling/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/node_modules/@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst cfg = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('/Users/ling/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'utf-8'));\n\nconst feishuCfg = cfg.channels.feishu;\nconst accounts = feishuCfg.accounts;\nconst mainAccount = accounts[feishuCfg.defaultAccount] || Object.values(accounts)[0];\n\nconst client = new Client({\n  appId: mainAccount.appId,\n  appSecret: mainAccount.appSecret,\n  domain: Domain.Feishu,\n});\n\nconst message = '🔴 策略参数巡检测试（Node.js SDK直发）';\nconst openId = 'ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae';\n\nclient.im.message.create({\n  params: { receive_id_type: 'open_id' },\n  data: {\n    receive_id: openId,\n    msg_type: 'text',\n    content: JSON.stringify({ text: message }),\n  }\n}).then(r => {\n  console.log('OK:', JSON.stringify(r.data));\n}).catch(e => {\n  console.log('Error:', e.message || e.response?.data);\n});\nEOF\nnode /tmp/test_lark_send.js 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":108308,"output":543,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476112344,"responseId":"0622d09003014dbc7f112110570cd8af"}}
