{"type":"message","id":"db4554b1","parentId":"8d345066","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:49:25.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing. The `feishu-assistant` app also can't send to this open_id.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The current session IS successfully sending to this open_id via the `message` tool. How does the `message` tool work? It's a tool provided by the OpenClaw runtime. The runtime has a Feishu plugin loaded.\n\nLet me look at the inbound context again. The current session has `account_id: \"coding-agent\"`. The `message` tool uses the runtime's feishu plugin to send. The plugin has the correct credentials for the coding-agent app (`cli_a934da0dde385cba`). And it CAN send to this open_id.Wait, but I also tried `cli_a934da0dde385cba` via the SDK and it failed. \n\nSo there's something different about how the runtime's Feishu plugin handles this—it must be using a different token or authentication method than what I'm testing with the SDK directly. Maybe the plugin has its own way of obtaining tokens that's separate from the standard app credentials.\n\nActually, I should step back and look at what's already working. The cron job runs Python scripts that successfully push to the existing target user `user:ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080`, so I should check how those scripts are actually sending messages—there's probably a Python library being used that I'm missing.","thinkingSignature":"368b0b861bd1ce8649138fbf840e12e2bc9434947beb5f70e6cde6049d3d43a3"},{"type":"text","text":"SDK 直发也失败。让我看看 cron 脚本里的 Python 是怎么成功推送的——那个 `push_to_feishu` 用的是什么：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_775sbjxwuomw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def push_to_feishu\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py 2>/dev/null | head -3; grep -n \"def.*push\\|def.*send\\|urllib\\|requests\\|http\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"#\\|class \" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109908,"output":444,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131819,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476150129,"responseId":"0622d0b69595100d28eb37e28fa61d0f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9901a62e","parentId":"db4554b1","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:49:25.589Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_775sbjxwuomw_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"50:def push_to_feishu(channel: str, account: str, target_user: str, message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple[bool, str]:\n50:def push_to_feishu(channel: str, account: str, target_user: str, message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple[bool, str]:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":21,"aggregated":"50:def push_to_feishu(channel: str, account: str, target_user: str, message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple[bool, str]:\n50:def push_to_feishu(channel: str, account: str, target_user: str, message: str, dry_run: bool = False) -> tuple[bool, str]:","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace-coding-agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775476165580}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b485388","parentId":"9901a62e","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:49:57.829Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `push_to_feishu` function in `report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py` uses `resolve_openclaw_bin()` to get the openclaw binary and then calls `openclaw message send`. So it uses the same CLI approach. And it sends to `user:ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080`. But when the CLI sends to this target, it works. But sending to `user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` fails with \"open_id cross app\".\n\nSo the issue is that the `ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080` open_id is valid for the main app, while `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` is NOT associated with the main app.\n \nThis open_id is probably tied to the coding-agent app instead. When I tested with the message tool, it worked because that tool uses the session's runtime context—which is configured with the OpenClaw feishu plugin that's actually logged into the correct app. So if the message tool has access to the right credentials, there might be a way to invoke it directly from Python.\n\nActually, looking at how `report_overnight_autopilot_if_armed.py` works, it just calls the `openclaw message send` CLI, which succeeds because the cron session itself must have the right plugin context. The cron wrapper doesn't specify `--account` explicitly, so it must be inheriting the feishu-assistant account configuration from somewhere, which is why it can send to `ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080` but not to `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae`.\n\nI'm stuck. The only account that can send to `ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae` is the one the current session is using, which is determined by how OpenClaw resolves the account from the incoming webhook event. I can't directly access that from a cron script. Let me try a different angle—what if I send a message to the same session instead?\n\nActually, the simplest solution is to update the target user to `user:ou_968a615509dc191f04220e18cda67080` and tell the user to check the group chat for strategy audit notifications. But they specifically asked for private chat delivery. I could explore using the user's chat ID instead of open_id, but I don't have access to that. Let me think about this differently—the `message` tool in the current session works fine, so maybe I should configure the cron script to write the message to a file and then I can pick it up and send it myself when I'm active.\n\nAlternatively, I could spawn myself as a subagent to send the message. But the simplest path forward is to confirm they received the test message and understand their preference: they want push notifications for strategy audit alerts. The challenge is that these alerts are generated by cron on Saturday mornings when they might not be available, so I need to figure out how to deliver them to their private Feishu account despite the account mismatch issue.\n\nI'm realizing I can configure the cron job itself to use the OpenClaw agent runtime instead of just running a Python script—this would let me use the message tool directly within the cron session. Let me try setting up a cron job with `--agent coding-agent --session isolated` so it runs in a proper agent context where the message tool would work.","thinkingSignature":"2e46d2b1800e46956733c0c2d79b5000c63ea4e36a211818b308842288ec0088"},{"type":"text","text":"让我换个思路——用 OpenClaw cron 的 agent 模式直接跑任务，这样就能用 message 工具推送：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hp9mbf0wv361_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"strategy-param-audit-feishu\" \\\n  --cron \"0 10 * * 6\" \\\n  --tz \"Asia/Shanghai\" \\\n  --agent \"coding-agent\" \\\n  --session \"isolated\" \\\n  --timeout-seconds 120 \\\n  --message \"运行策略参数自动巡检并推送结果：\\n\\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/run_strategy_param_auto_audit.py --force-report\\n\\n如果推送失败，读取生成的 research/reports/strategy_param_auto_audit_YYYYMMDD.md 文件，通过飞书私聊（user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae）发送告警摘要。\" \\\n  2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106855,"output":993,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476165591,"responseId":"0622d0c5bd214d44651f64c7c6810dc5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5cefbd4","parentId":"8b485388","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:49:58.825Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hp9mbf0wv361_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"a7b9828d-8e45-4e4e-b69e-be8d13e768b9\",\n  \"agentId\": \"coding-agent\",\n  \"name\": \"strategy-param-audit-feishu\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775476198792,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1775476198792,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 10 * * 6\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"运行策略参数自动巡检并推送结果：\\\\n\\\\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/run_strategy_param_auto_audit.py --force-report\\\\n\\\\n如果推送失败，读取生成的 research/reports/strategy_param_auto_audit_YYYYMMDD.md 文件，通过飞书私聊（user:ou_47c21eede907b0c4f9fd4d34519d84ae）发送告警摘要。\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"last\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1775872800000\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":985,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"a7b9828d-8e45-4e4e-b69e-be8d13e768b9\",\n  \"agentId\": \"coding-agent\",\n  \"name\": \"strategy-param-audit-feishu\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775476198792,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1775476198792,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 10 * * 6\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"运行策略参数自动巡检并推送结果：\\\\n\\\\ncd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/run_strategy_param_auto_audit.py --force-report\\\\n\\\\n如果推送失败，读取生成的 research/reports/strategy_param_auto_audit_YYYYMMDD.md 文件，通过飞书私聊（user:ou