{"type":"message","id":"f4d29026","parentId":"e2b3661b","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:53:04.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `crontab -l` shows nothing and exit code is 0. This means the crontab IS empty. The issue is that `crontab -l` showed a bunch of entries earlier, but now it's empty. Wait, actually exit code 0 with no output could mean:1. The crontab is truly empty2. The `crontab -` (stdin) was used and received no input, and `crontab -l` then returned empty\n\nLet me check by directly looking at the crontab file:","thinkingSignature":"593a040819f6020e6bf9d516689eef9a2e2bc63a1783cbc430e80c99c68601ec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o1exa0vt9k2v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /usr/lib/cron/tabs/ling 2>/dev/null || ls -la /var/spool/cron/crontabs/ling 2>/dev/null || find / -name \"ling\" -path \"*/cron*\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107553,"output":203,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476378120,"responseId":"0622d19a1ff469926007eb9b40928729"}}
