{"type":"message","id":"64c124ae","parentId":"2d052940","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:53:48.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the system crontab seems to have been cleared. Let me check what I actually need to restore. From memory, the system crontab had entries like SHADOWROCKET_NODE_SYNC. But actually, looking at the OpenClaw cron list, there's already a `shadowrocket-node-sync-0900` there... wait, no that has a different name. Let me check more carefully.\n\nActually, the system `crontab -l` entries I saw earlier could have been from a different user or from launchd. On macOS, `crontab` is deprecated in favor of `launchd`. So the `crontab -l` output I saw might have been from an actual crontab that existed.\n\n\nNow I need to figure out what was actually in that crontab before I cleared it. The shadowrocket entry I saw earlier might have been using OpenClaw's own scheduling rather than the system crontab, so let me trace back what commands were actually in there.","thinkingSignature":"940c1036b7c4f8786b7b73a2ceeb5f40cde555c89517d666a4424584c47aabf7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wysw1ceiub8i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/workout_reminder.sh 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; ls /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/*.sh 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":105784,"output":287,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127538,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476415257,"responseId":"0622d1bf13be907e1eda3a0e436357ff"}}
