{"type":"message","id":"e5f80c42","parentId":"9892918c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:54:25.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that these install scripts add entries to the system crontab. Since the system crontab seems empty now, I should reinstall the necessary ones. But actually, let me check: if the system crontab was empty when I ran the `grep -v | crontab -` command, then my command would have correctly (but unnecessarily) set an empty crontab. The previous entries must have been there before...\n\nActually wait - let me re-examine. The command I ran was:\n```\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"STRATEGY_PARAM_AUTO_AUDIT_SAT_1000\" | crontab - && echo \"已删除...\"\n\n\n```\n\nIf the crontab had only the STRATEGY_PARAM_AUTO_AUDIT_SAT_1000 entry, then grep -v would have removed it, leaving nothing to pipe to `crontab -`, which would set an empty crontab. That would explain why everything's gone now.\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw cron list to see if those entries are still there - they use a separate system, so they should be independent of what I did with the system crontab.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"0251e4bda097af38547cfd756f2a87fa9fbcba6adf52ab6711b332cf822e2f07"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mtjvg5onxgqp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron list 2>/dev/null | grep \"PAPER_V1_INTRADAY\\|CONSERVATIVE_SHADOW\\|QUANT_PANELS_1610\\|WORKOUT_REMINDER\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107445,"output":321,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775476455632,"responseId":"0622d1e7951ec500e082a1f10f34cef6"}}
