{"type":"message","id":"2a275a41","parentId":"e8b66e96","timestamp":"2026-04-06T12:31:01.283Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the existing format. Now let me design the weekly hypothesis generation script. The key idea is:\n\n1. Read recent data (walk-forward results, paper trading NAV, market breadth, experiment registry)\n2. Analyze patterns: what's working, what's not\n3. Generate 3-5 new strategy hypotheses\n4. Write to a hypothesis file\n\nLet me also look at the candidate_pool structure to understand what's there.","thinkingSignature":"e460feb550248b036bd2496aa61bbcc605f1137386663fd921f4c4631e6a507f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9f3ugept2nb8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/candidate_pool_20260403.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in d.items() if k in ['generated_at','strategy_summary','hypothesis_candidates','new_findings']}, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:2000])\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106952,"output":220,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128639,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775478650032,"responseId":"0622da7b8de049f51d8f5da8a4eb1457"}}
