{"type":"message","id":"b6351809","parentId":"976d9ad0","timestamp":"2026-04-06T12:31:57.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:1. Create a shell wrapper\n2. Add an OpenClaw cron for Saturday 16:00\n3. The script itself just prepares context - the actual hypothesis generation is done by the AI agent\n\nBut actually, since the script needs to use AI to generate hypotheses (it's not a deterministic script), I should make this an agent-based cron rather than a Python script cron. The Python script prepares context files, and the agent reads them and generates the actual hypotheses.\n\nLet me think about this differently:\n- The Python script `run_strategy_hypothesis_weekly.py` prepares context and writes it to files\n\n\n- Then the OpenClaw agent cron runs and generates the hypotheses, writes them to `hypothesis/YYYYMMDD_hypotheses.md`, and pushes alerts to Feishu\n\nI need to set up the OpenClaw cron to trigger this workflow every Saturday at 16:00.","thinkingSignature":"40bd314f041508b03fbbbd5745e22d7463684cf603f0daa5ee7431f61bf43626"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g2qjqsc906wz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -m py_compile /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_strategy_hypothesis_weekly.py && echo \"语法OK\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107933,"output":252,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129652,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775478705352,"responseId":"0622dab2056b0c78b3385624ced31f4a"}}
