{"type":"message","id":"f9f986e4","parentId":"b7e9acc7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:22:04.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the system. The `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` script generates the \"全球宏观对冲研报\" - it monitors Weibo, collects intelligence about tariffs, geopolitics, etc., and generates a structured report.The user wants to optimize the pre-open report. Let me understand what they mean. Looking at the image, the card is a nicely formatted Feishu interactive card about global macro topics (tariffs, US markets, China market, gold). The current `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` generates this kind of report.\n\nThe user's feedback about \"优化盘前报告\" probably means:1. The report in the image (from aggregate_intelligence_brief.py) is already quite good - it's rich and structured\n\n\n2. But the `investment_research_background_cycle` report (which I saw earlier) is much simpler and less informative\n3. The user wants the cycle report to be improved OR wants the intelligence report to be further optimized\n\nThe core issue is that the intelligence report currently lacks the specific stock recommendations - it covers global macro themes but doesn't show which positions to take or what signals are triggering those calls.\n\nLooking at what's actually needed: the pre-open report needs clearer separation between the macro view and actionable stock signals, should reference today's trading parameters, and could pull in the convertible bond market temperature data that's already being collected. The existing framework might already have some of this capability, so the question is whether to extend what's there or build something new to bridge the macro intelligence with specific tradeable ideas. Looking at what's actually in the current pre-open reports, I need to figure out what would make them genuinely more useful—the macro section is solid, but the stock signals are vague and there's no clear trading edge. 