{"type":"message","id":"d2ee8340","parentId":"f9e27f09","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:34:46.525Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log shows that there's a conflict between two running processes trying to download data simultaneously. Also, there's a tushare API error - the daily data for the 000852.SH index is failing with `ERROR - data_url: request tushare pro api failed: 抱歉，每分钟最多访问200次...`. This is a rate limit issue.\n\nThe last successful daily download was `2026-04-02`. So there's no data for 2026-04-03 and 2026-04-06 (today).\n\nSince today is a holiday (no trading), the data for 2026-04-03 (yesterday) might be the last trading day data we need to ensure is captured.\n \nI see the issue now - the 2026-03-03 cutoff in the walk-forward refers to the training window end date, not the actual market data cutoff. The Qlib data should extend through 2026-04-03 as the last trading day before today.\n\nLet me prioritize what I can realistically accomplish tonight: enhancing the aggregate intelligence brief and refreshing the Qlib data, though the rate limiting on the tushare API is going to be a constraint.","thinkingSignature":"0c471a224eb1dd034e6e4ae4d392131d20275af6237b66887ec9736f0c2a3875"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c3xnlkubuxi7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/daily_quant_analysis_skill_20260403.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\n# 找数据日期标签\nprint('trade_date_tag:', d.get('trade_date_tag'))\nprint('trade_date:', d.get('trade_date'))\nfresh = d.get('data_freshness', {})\nprint('mismatched:', fresh.get('mismatched_required_inputs', []))\nprint('missing:', fresh.get('missing_required_inputs', []))\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":123439,"output":397,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":1