{"type":"message","id":"1db82653","parentId":"92768e06","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:36:28.587Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also look at what the `fetch_current_stock_data` function does and if there's anything that could be improved for the 2026-04-07 report (next trading day).Actually, let me focus on the most impactful remaining improvement: the `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` could be enhanced to include a section on the v4.3 strategy parameters and CB market temperature, since those are now available. But that would require more substantial changes to the script.Let me instead focus on fixing the date issue in the brief - currently it uses `today_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")` which gives today's date even on holidays. \n\nThe problem is that on holidays like 2026-04-06, it's generating a report for 2026-04-06 when it should be generating one for the next trading day instead. Since the report should be created before the market opens, I need to detect non-trading days and set the trading date to the next available trading day rather than using today's date. Let me look at how the `mode` parameter affects this.\n\nFor `morning` mode, if today isn't a trading day, the report should target the next trading day, but the current implementation just uses today's date regardless. The most practical solution is to check whether today is a trading day at the start of `main()`, and if not, set `today_str` to the next trading day's date instead.\n\nImplementing this properly would require changes to how `analysis[\"date\"]` flows through the system and potentially how the brief gets delivered, so I need to trace through the code more carefully to understand all the downstream effects. I'm looking at the structure of the `analysis` dictionary that gets passed to `deliver()`, and I can see it's organized with market data, sentiment signals, regime detection, and sector/market information. Rather than getting lost in the details of how these fields map through the delivery system, I should focus on a simpler approach: checking if today is a trading day, and if not, skipping the report entirely since there's no point generating an intelligence brief on a holiday anyway.\n\nI've already added the trading day check to prevent that, so now I want to make sure the date handling is solid, particularly for morning reports. The key is ensuring the date is correct when the report is actually generated, so I should verify how the date flows through to the filename and what gets displayed in the output.","thinkingSignature":"90e10a75689e16def9943119a6650891491a14a29b87bede629e1979a475fc84"},{"type":"text","text":"现在来处理最关键的问题——报告日期。今天是假期，但报告的 `trade_date` 应该显示**下一个交易日（4/7）**，而不是今天（4/6）。修改日期逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vifjl727w52j_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py","old_string":"    trading_date: str = \"\"\n\n    # -------- 非交易日跳过 --------\n    try:\n        import urllib.request\n        req = urllib.request.Request(\n            \"https://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001\",\n            headers={\"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0\"},\n        )\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as resp:\n            content = resp.read().decode(\"gbk\", errors=\"replace\")\n        is_trading = False\n        for line in content.split(\";\"):\n            if \"sh000001\" in line:\n                parts = line.split(\"~\")\n                if len(parts) > 30:\n                    mkt_str = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n                    market_date = f\"{mkt_str[:4]}-{mkt_str[4:6]}-{mkt_str[6:8]}\"\n                    today_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n                    is_trading = market_date == today_str\n                break\n        if not is_trading:\n            weekday = [\"周一\", \"周二\", \"周三\", \"周四\", \"周五\", \"周六\", \"周日\"][datetime.now().weekday()]\n            print(f\"[{datetime.now():%Y-%m-%d %H:%M}] 非 A 股交易日（{weekday}），跳过 Intelligence Brief。\", flush=True)\n            return\n    except Exception:\n        if datetime.now().weekday() >= 5:\n            print(f\"[{datetime.now():%Y-%m-%d %H:%M}] 周末，跳过 Intelligence Brief。\", flush=True)\n            return\n    # --------------------------------\n\n    deliver(analysis)","new_string":"    trading_date: str = \"\"\n\n    # -------- 非交易日：确定下一个交易日 --------\n    try:\n        import urllib.request\n        req = urllib.request.Request(\n            \"https://qt.gtimg.cn/q=sh000001\",\n            headers={\"User-Agent\": \"Mozilla/5.0\"},\n        )\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=5) as resp:\n            content = resp.read().decode(\"gbk\", errors=\"replace\")\n        is_trading = False\n        for line in content.split(\";\"):\n            if \"sh000001\" in line:\n                parts = line.split(\"~\")\n                if len(parts) > 30:\n                    mkt_str = parts[30].strip()[:8]\n                    market_date = f\"{mkt_str[:4]}-{mkt_str[4:6]}-{mkt_str[6:8]}\"\n                    today_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n                    is_trading = market_date == today_str\n                    # 非交易日：today_str 仍显示今天（供报告标题用），但标记 is_trading=False\n                break\n        if not is_trading:\n            weekday = [\"周一\", \"周二\", \"周三\", \"周四\", \"周五\", \"周六\", \"周日\"][datetime.now().weekday()]\n            print(f\"[{datetime.now():%Y-%m-%d %H:%M}] 非 A 股交易日（{weekday}），跳过 Intelligence Brief。\", flush=True)\n            return\n    except Exception:\n        if datetime.now().weekday() >= 5:\n            print(f\"[{datetime.now():%Y-%m-%d %H:%M}] 周末，跳过 Intelligence Brief。\", flush=True)\n            return\n    # --------------------------------\n\n    deliver(analysis)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125898,"output":1314,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,