{"type":"message","id":"c6f5c31e","parentId":"e54bde04","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:36:35.876Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I just reverted the logic to the original - the issue is that I need to keep the logic I added but also ensure the date handling is correct. Let me re-read the current state.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the current code has `today_str = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")` inside the for loop, which is fine for normal days. On non-trading days, it returns early (as I added). So the main issue was just the non-trading day execution, which is now fixed.\n\nLet me verify the syntax is still OK.","thinkingSignature":"221b7e18bcaf9df5bcdb0a98a75450096dc91cc2202047c631943e0aaac8cd40"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kxbf7k1l0dt3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -m py_compile /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py && echo \"语法OK\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":127237,"output":176,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148880,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482588626,"responseId":"0622e9dd463e0e353be0b7bac7f74b5b"}}
