{"type":"message","id":"faca55e2","parentId":"64ce17e2","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:36:48.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also look at what the Qlib data staleness issue is. The problem is that the latest trading data is from 2026-04-03 (Thursday), and today is 2026-04-06 (Monday, holiday). So tomorrow (2026-04-07) should have data from 2026-04-03 being the last trading day.\n\nThe walk-forward data was generated with `period end=2026-03-03`. This means the latest window only has data up to 2026-03-03. This is a data cutoff issue - the Qlib database needs to be updated to include more recent data.\n\n\nI'm realizing the 2026-04-03 data might actually be incomplete since the walk-forward generator filters for complete 60-trading-day windows, and 2026-03-03 is right after a holiday period. I should check what data is actually available in the Qlib database to understand the full extent of what's missing.","thinkingSignature":"fc93634acfaca46a850ec517be5040b30848301cf38d484a56a1370893f348cd"},{"type":"text","text":"最后，检查一下 Qlib 数据的实际情况，看明天报告能覆盖到哪天：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_23hnu7dhra78_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport os\nos.environ['QLIB_DIR'] = '/Users/ling/.qlib/qlib_data/cn_data'\nimport qlib\nqlib.init()\nfrom qlib.data import D\ncalendar = D.trading_days(start_time='2026-03-01', end_time='2026-04-10')\ndates = [str(d)[:10] for d in calendar]\nprint('Qlib交易日期（3月至今）:')\nfor d in dates:\n    print(d)\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":127438,"output":361,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":149266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482595957,"responseId":"0622e9e46e58d17fbabad97dcab92e17"}}
