{"type":"message","id":"67289255","parentId":"1e7eacf5","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:37:00.893Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The qlib calendar shows that 2026-04-06 (today) IS a trading day according to the calendar. But the Tencent API showed that today's data is not available (清明节). This means the qlib calendar is WRONG - it includes 2026-04-06 as a trading day, but the market was actually closed for Qingming.\n\nThis is a known issue - qlib's calendar might not be updated for holidays. The Tencent API showed the latest market date as 20260403, confirming 2026-04-06 is a holiday.\n\nThis means my trading day check using Tencent API is correct, and qlib's calendar is outdated.\n\n\nThe walk-forward summary confirms the training data ends at 2026-03-03, so the breadth and Qlib signals would only reflect data through early March, which explains why the walk-forward windows have such short 50-day periods ending in early March. The data freshness checks are already in place to flag this staleness, so I'll commit these final fixes now.","thinkingSignature":"5a011e4da3027cfebcc1727a22709516ad941687a62061ae868f9e318defd268"},{"type":"text","text":"发现一个重要问题：**Qlib 日历把今天（4/6）当作交易日了，但实际是清明节休市**。这导致 walk-forward 窗口可能比想象的还短。这是 Qlib 内置日历没有更新节假日的问题，先记住，以后修复。\n\n提交今天最后的修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m52agss51m86_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && git add scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py && git diff --cached --stat"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":127824,"output":329,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":149620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482609630,"responseId":"0622e9f29424a3a00a4d757f28a7842a"}}
