{"type":"message","id":"bfb9cd49","parentId":"d5929b76","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:39:31.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the paper trading profiles script uses `deliver_report_to_feishu()`. Let me look at what the `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh` actually does and what messages it produces. The main issue seems to be that the paper profiles cron generates a lot of output but the messages are not well formatted for quick consumption.\n\nLet me also look at the `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.py` to understand what it pushes, and the `generate_paper_trading_comparison_dashboard.py`.\n\nActually, I think the most impactful things to optimize are:\n1. **Paper Profiles cron** - generates too much text, hard to read quickly\n\n\n2. **Data source health probe** - often noisy with price divergence alerts\n3. **盘前日报 (daily brief)** - we already optimized this\n4. **盘中值班 (background cycle)** - what does this push?\n\nLet me check what the background cycle pushes.","thinkingSignature":"0b8eb7a825d6daefd64866456823d0f452c06c10b1c63616dce90b4f42784d81"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dba53iz1rs4b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"feishu\\|post\\|send\\|deliver\\|notify\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_investment_research_background_cycle.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"def \\|#\" | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":128171,"output":273,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":149911,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482760444,"responseId":"0622ea8927d23fc70343e1aae903b676"}}
