{"type":"message","id":"56e51095","parentId":"92486422","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:39:56.764Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so `report_delivery.py` uses `feishu_client.feishu_post()` with `msg_type=\"interactive\"` and `card_type=\"news\"`. This means all the reports are being sent as Feishu interactive cards.\n\nThe key scripts that push to Feishu:\n1. `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` - Global macro, Trump tariff news (good quality)\n2. `run_investment_research_data_source_health_probe.py` - Data source health (often noisy)\n3. `run_investment_research_event_watch.py` - Temporary meeting/conference alerts\n4. `run_investment_research_background_cycle.py` - Trading session duty reports\n\n\n5. `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.py` - Paper trading comparison dashboard (can be verbose)\n6. `run_intraday_risk_recheck.py` - Intraday risk review\n7. `run_close_review_v2.py` - Close review\n\nThe main sources of noise are the paper trading dashboard which generates excessive text, the data source health probe that frequently triggers false alerts, and the background cycle reports that could be more concise. I should focus on streamlining these three.\n\nThe paper trading comparison dashboard is the most critical to address since it produces dense output every morning, followed by the data source probe which generates alerts about price discrepancies that aren't always actionable, and then the background cycle reports.","thinkingSignature":"01f3c720348723376deb0b244622572a1a3ee8f5d0dbc60d25170ac7c78cb78f"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。主要噪音来源是这几个 cron。让我看一下它们现在的消息质量：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0084mic5df6i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -60 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_paper_trading_comparison_dashboard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":128729,"output":365,"cacheRead"