{"type":"message","id":"301e8706","parentId":"2788ee4a","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:40:19.599Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure. The key things to optimize are:\n\n1. **Paper trading profiles**: Make the card more compact, highlight v4_3, add TL;DR\n2. **Data source health probe**: Make it less noisy - only send for serious issues (not just \"watch_guarded\")\n3. **Background cycle**: Simplify the output\n\nFor the paper trading dashboard, the card is already an interactive card. The key improvement would be to add a TL;DR section and highlight v4_3 prominently.\n\nFor the data source health probe, I can add a `--min-severity` argument and only send messages for serious issues.\n\n\nI'll start with the data source health probe since it's the noisiest component, then move to the paper trading dashboard and background cycle. Let me examine the `run_data_source_health.py` to understand the full logic before making changes.","thinkingSignature":"2568330ac35f89a72c0b414964b652f4c6a252149e810f405216f0f409fa50ea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bbh1k45xlgi3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -50 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_data_source_health.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":129498,"output":235,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":151200,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482809711,"responseId":"0622eabaa4253679879e6f34613f3ec6"}}
