{"type":"message","id":"d73e36d8","parentId":"d02474bc","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:41:04.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I can see the `deliver_paper_comparison_to_feishu` function. It builds a Feishu interactive card with a header, and a table with columns: Profile, NAV, Total Return, Annual Return, Sharpe, Max Drawdown, Status. Then it sends the top holdings for each profile.\n\nThe main issues:\n1. **Paper profiles cron**: Every morning it sends a card with all 3 profiles (defensive, balanced, aggressive). But now we only care about v4_3. Also the holdings list is very verbose.\n2. **Data source health**: Sends cards even for `watch_guarded` status (not critical)\n\n\n3. **Background cycle**: Sends cards for 3 sessions (pre-open 08:40, intraday 10:30, close 16:30)\n\nI think the best approach is to tackle the paper profiles first since that's the highest volume, then focus on making the data source health alerts more actionable by only flagging critical issues. For paper profiles specifically, I should surface v4_3 prominently, add a TL;DR summary at the top, trim down the holdings section, and maybe consolidate the 3-session background cycle into one daily digest instead of three separate cards.\n\nLet me map out what each script currently pushes so I can see where the real inefficiencies are.","thinkingSignature":"1e915945a48b02072d9a4a17161ed1e4002d6af5798299d250ac37260e529fa6"},{"type":"text","text":"我现在清楚问题在哪里了。让我一次性把三个最嘈杂的推送优化掉：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4yow2y1j5353_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/paper_profile_utils.py | grep -n \"card_type\\|msg_type\\|paper_profile\\|deliver\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":130499,"output":364,"cacheRead":21467,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":152330,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482850695,"responseId":"0622eae373e0130a29a2309cba571613"}}
